                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6180.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-18T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 18, 1913—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Your February 16, 11 a.m. The Department compliments you upon your success in
                    arranging an armistice and the prompt and efficient way in which foreigners were
                    removed from danger zones and arrangements were made for the transportation of
                    American women and children to the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Note.</hi>—At this point a military interregnum occurs,
                        lasting a day and a half.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
